## Scheduled automation (launchd)

Loops restart automatically on macOS login via LaunchAgent `com.chitwan.instructor-automation`. Scripts are installed to `~/Library/Application Support/instructor-automation/scripts/` (macOS blocks launchd from Desktop). Re-install after script changes: `.cursor/scripts/install-instructor-automation.sh`.

| Schedule | Script | Skill |
|----------|--------|-------|
| Daily 09:00 IST | `.cursor/scripts/daily-slack-loop.sh` | `daily-slack-review` |
| Sunday 09:00 IST | `.cursor/scripts/sunday-feedback-loop.sh` | `classroom-feedback-analysis` |

When a tick fires, it is appended to `~/Library/Application Support/instructor-automation/pending-ticks.jsonl` and a macOS notification is shown. The `.cursor/hooks.json` `stop` hook drains one pending tick per agent completion (up to 3 chained runs).

**On any conversation in this repo:** if the pending queue is non-empty, process all queued ticks first (run the skill prompt, send Slack DM) unless the user explicitly needs something else urgently.

Logs: `~/Library/Logs/instructor-automation/`. Stop loops: `.cursor/scripts/stop-instructor-loops.sh`.

